From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Juan Sanchez Fuentes <juanesf91@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 20:15:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] mmc: skip CMD16 (SET_BLOCKLEN) for SDHC/SDXC cards

Per the SD specification, SDHC/SDXC cards always use a fixed 512-byte
block length regardless of CMD16.  Some cards (and the Allwinner A523
SoC MMC controller) fail CMD16 after a fresh controller reset even
though the identification sequence succeeded.  Skip CMD16 for
high-capacity cards requesting the mandatory 512-byte block size,
matching the Linux kernel behavior.

Signed-off-by: Juan Sanchez Fuentes <juanesf91@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/mmc.c | 11 +++++++++++
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/mmc.c b/drivers/mmc/mmc.c
index bf82c515600..c092ba26c8e 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/mmc.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/mmc.c
@@ -357,6 +357,17 @@ int mmc_set_blocklen(struct mmc *mmc, int len)
 	if (mmc->ddr_mode)
 		return 0;
 
+	/*
+	 * Per the SD specification, SDHC/SDXC cards always use a fixed
+	 * 512-byte block length regardless of CMD16.  Some cards (and
+	 * the A523 SoC MMC controller) fail CMD16 after a fresh reset
+	 * even though the identification sequence succeeded.  Skip
+	 * CMD16 for high-capacity cards requesting the mandatory
+	 * 512-byte block size - matches the Linux kernel.
+	 */
+	if (mmc->high_capacity && len == 512)
+		return 0;
+
 	cmd.cmdidx = MMC_CMD_SET_BLOCKLEN;
 	cmd.resp_type = MMC_RSP_R1;
 	cmd.cmdarg = len;
